net.proteusframework.core.locale.annotation

Annotation Type I18NFile


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
@Documented
@Retention(value=SOURCE)
public @interface I18NFile
    Use to define a set of internalization records that will go in a file.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      I18N[] i18n
      Internationalization records.
      java.lang.String symbolPrefix

    • Element Detail

      • i18n

        public abstract I18N[] i18n
        Internationalization records.
        Returns:
        one or more records.

      • symbolPrefix

        public abstract java.lang.String symbolPrefix
        The symbol prefix. This is prepended to all symbols defined in I18Ns on the same ElementType.PACKAGE or ElementType.TYPE. It is used to namespace I18N records to avoid collisions.

        Do NOT change the prefix once in use without providing a data conversion.

        Returns:
        the prefix. Non-empty string.

      • classVisibility

        public abstract I18NFile.Visibility classVisibility
        Visibility of generated class. Defaults to I18NFile.Visibility.PACKAGE.
        Returns:
        the class visibility.
        Default:
        net.proteusframework.core.locale.annotation.I18NFile.Visibility.PACKAGE

      • file

        public abstract java.lang.String file
        File name. Optional if used on a Java Class. If used on a package via I18NFiles, it is required. This is used to generate the Java Class for referencing the LocalizedObjectKeys as well as the XML file that stores the localizations for the JDBCLocaleSource.
        Returns:
        If empty, the default, a file name is generated based on where the annotation is placed.
        Default:
        ""
